Obviously not. The monster just roared and tried to charge directly at Sasalin. Thank goodness, Sasalin, although large in size, was still flexible enough to dodge in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream, almost slipping down the smooth scales of Sasalin.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Aim for their heads!"
"It's too difficult!"
Sasalin roared, circled around, and flew toward the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely, but when it was attacked by fire from behind, it seemed a bit panicked. This monster had not yet realized it now had another opponent. Sasalin slowed down and then hit the monster's head with its tail, knocking it off course, making the monster even more panicked.
The monster roared, emitting a hissing sound from its throat, flying straight upward while continuously spitting something into the air. Suddenly, the surroundings turned pitch black, as if the monster was absorbing the light from the sky and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasalin suddenly went blind, trying to step back but found himself colliding with the branches and then falling to the ground. The monster seemed to know exactly where Sasalin had fallen and flew straight toward him, dragging the dark cloud along with it.
"Kael!" Tenuk screamed, flying out of the dark cloud and beginning to circle, trying to locate Nishi and Sasalin in the darkness below. "What should we do? Kael...? Kael, where are you?"
Nishi struggled to stand up. She felt certain she had broken some bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability had already started to take effect. Sasalin's condition was different; he lay helplessly on the ground, leaning against a tree he had knocked over. Nishi tried to move toward Sasalin, but her vision was completely dark, almost nothing visible. Everywhere were terrible shadows, and something was screaming within them.
A terrifying club-shaped tail suddenly smashed onto the ground, knocking Nishi over. She noticed the tail was swinging wildly, but its target seemed not to be her. Nishi barely saw the monster roaring and clawing at the shadows it had created with its claws. Something was teleporting through the darkness, waiting for the right moment to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot split the air, and the monster immediately fell silent, lying motionless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth of the situation. Kael stood on top of the monster's corpse, holding a rifle, breathing heavily.
"That was... it was one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tanto Katerolon..." Kael gasped for breath. Somehow, his eyes glowed with black light, and a surge of dark energy flowed within him. But just as Kael was about to speak, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
A while later, Nisi finally understood what had happened. They all knew that Kael possessed eerie shadow abilities, but he rarely used them because most people considered this ability extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nisi didn't know that Kael could use this ability in any darkness. Moreover, from Kael's performance, it seemed that he was also quite surprised himself.
"Are you okay?" Nisi couldn't help asking.
"I'm fine. I've killed that thing, and I'll be alright soon." Kael looked at his "masterpiece," at which moment, Tenuk landed beside him, reverting back to his original Spartan form.
Now, the monster is no longer moving, and they can finally take a good look at what it really is. Its skin is dark and shiny, covered with a layer of sticky liquid, which is firmly attached to the monster's body. It has four wings and four legs, with long claws at the end of each leg, and two straight horns on its skull.
Teunuk and Kayer hadn't even had time to ask what the hell this thing was when another monster suddenly jumped out from the nearby bushes. At that moment, a familiar car collided with the monster's side, causing it to slide for a distance before stopping by Nisi's feet. Nisi didn't hesitate and grabbed the shotgun, firing a shot at the monster's head, killing it instantly.
"Oh...," Rettwick muttered as he sat in the driver's seat, then awkwardly turned off the engine and got out of the truck. "Er, I didn't mean to do that. Are you all okay?"
"You missed all the fun!" Teunuk said with a sigh. "Where were you?"
"You left me behind," Rettwick sighed. "I tried my best to catch up... Please, what are these terrible things?"
Retvik's question was answered by Sassalin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, looked a bit dizzy, but the injuries didn't seem serious.
"You killed the corrupted ones! Those infected monsters. When the corruption attacked your god, these creatures were left behind here."
"You mean... we... helped kill the terrible monster god?" Tenuk stammered a bit.
"Yes, that's exactly right. There might be more corrupted ones. But I can't shoot them in the head. I don't have a gun. And fighting two on one isn't fair, right?" Sassalin walked up to Kayel and patted his head. "Thank you, little guy. You made me think of my old friend Arcadin. Although you aren't as ruthless as him, nor do you have his ability to destroy the universe."
"Eh... thank you... I think..." Kayel shrugged. "So, uh, did we complete the mission?"
Nisi shrugged her shoulders, picked up the camera, and took a few photos of the monsters that were clearly already dead. Then, she pulled out her favorite dagger—the elegant Death's Dagger—and began cutting off one of the monsters' horns, then another. However, the moment Nisi finished cutting, the monsters suddenly caught fire and quickly turned into a pile of ashes. The horns she had cut off also turned to ashes.
"Well... this is definitely a mix of good and bad..." Nisi sighed. "At least I still have the photos, right?"
